I MOVE!
To  ANOTHERSUNYDAY
*Note i do realise that sunny is misspelt, but some other fucker with better grammar got their first.

SO JOIN ME!
Or don't.. But please do?

Today was a nice day.

Pretty mucb no one was there due to some excursion.

My glue had leaked due to some dude breaking it. NO MORE WARM BABY:(

We got kicked out of our spot, for the "Inability to keep it spotless". this frustrates me because litter is revolting, and as such i always pick up after myself. and it is upsetting that some people are too ignorant and selfish to do the same.
So i was lost today. Homeless.
At lunch Ajax and I went to the drawing room (it was warm there). We got stuff from outside and used the squishing thing to squish it. Twas fun. And he made a face out a wire and pliers. and i saw his big artwork. and then some teacher whom i'd never seen before came in because class was about to start, and she knew my name! i was obviously freaked out. 

Arr get away songs that aren't belle!

Nothing could make me upset today because of Belle. And I found myself to be less shy and more talkative than usual. I thank Belle for this. When I was bored i drew pictures of Judy and her Dream Of Horses. I wish I was in Sydney right now, for obvious reasons. Ok you can slap me for not shutting up about it, whatever. 

But Don't be like that woman on the train yesterday who was frustrated with my happiness.

i've been having strange dreams lately.

last night i dreamt rats were infesting my house and i was too scared too sleep so i got my dog to lie on my bed because i thought she would detect the rats, but she didn't and then i was outside my house and jumping on some person's back because the rats were scaring me.

and the night before

i was at school and i asked amy if she wanted to do something whenever and then jess appeared out of nowhere behind amy and was like no! amy cannot go she has to watch me absail. and then it changed to me and me cous jamie for some reason were at school. at first we were in that computer room in star downstairs... i don't know how to describe it more.  richard kingsmill was our teacher and he said we were doing an experiment and that jamie had to be addicted to drugs so we could see what happened. so then jamie came back with a large stack of plastic cups (?) and then we were going to the toilet where i passed a room where mit and stephanie baker were doing the can-can. and i stopped and laughed. and when i got out  of the toilets, which were like these big fucking  holes and i think it was similar to st james toilets (except they were holes), we were in bentleigh and then we turned a corner and it was degraves st and jamie said something like "wheres the big circus that was here during the commonwealth games?"

then i woke up.

today was psychology.

it was ok.

except i may end up on the dole as i didn't know what a k complex or sleep spindle was.

i also had my photog exam. it was incredibly hard. i don't know how to analysis photographs. i also don't care about technological advances in photography.

exams are finished.

i think that is the main thing.

eww my psych exam is on tueday. watch 30% of my mark fly away in under 2 hours. 

hehe i was doing some practice exam the other day and the question said something like

"Suki had her corpus callosum cut...blah blah"

anyway..  i laughed and wrote. Sukie was a kid and she liked to hang out in the graveyard  A+ for grace's psychology knowledge!

and b&s is NEXT FREAKING WEEK. i still have no id. die die die i possibly shall. 

now i have to go DO HOMEWORK. cause i have.no.life


seriously.i almost enjoy the lack of life.



almost.

grr i have to somehow write an essay on donnie darko. it is a lot harder than it maybe seems... espeically seeing as the essay topic is so stupid. annoyance.

today i went to buy two cds. for some reason they were reduced. i'm not sure why. it was one of those moments where you go to register and it's magically less than you thought it would be. it made me happy.

the dancing milk is so hypnotic. it reminds me of the funky moves that i could do IF i get into belle and seb. arr arr arrr. (extreme annoyance. anyone got id they wanna give me??? :))


hmm maybe that is all. 


except exams are soon and I'M GOING TO DIE.

grr a decision

do i want to go see Ben Folds and the Melbourne symphony orchestra at hamer hall in september?

OR

Robbie Williams at Telstra Dome in December?

tickets are somewhat cheaper to folds, and certaintly a lot easier to get... BUT... it's robbie.... 
...if only i had money to afford both.



Psych thing today wasn't bad. well at good as spending 4.5 hours of my weekend on school related tasks can be. except man was the last guy boring. i actually felt sorry for him as large amounts of people were leaving. and all that talk about sleep made me so so tired.

i think i may kill psych.
yes. the subject.
as writing era's are generally the most boring thing ever. who cares how past experience influences interpretations of ambiguous stimuli? not fucking me. there are simply TOO MANY big words in that sentence. it.hurts.my.head.

grr grr grr.

i had a happy and generally pleasant birthday. though eggs floretine is nowhere near as nice as it sounds. photo booths are love though eh?

and yes. my school is far untrusting of their kids. and grr. I NEED FAKE ID FOR BELLE AND SEBASTIAN. maybe it only just dawned on me that it's freaking soon. and i need to get in.

So today was my birthday.
here are some things that happened...

i felt obliged to eat chocolate cake twice even though i dislike it (ok the second time was actually damn good cake)

i submerged my hand into a gutter streaming with water not once but twice then ran after the water down the road when a car beeped at me for no reason (i was still ON The footpath, and i dropped my ring)

i ate lots.

i got a bracelet made out of a fork from ajax

i sung in the rain

i watched a fight evolve between eva and some old woman. 

my ego got boosted to extreme new heights.

my dinner got paid for me.

i had fun! (hehe)

ok
I've decided that i need to stop being so judgemental of people. I'm sure there are probably people laughing at me because I don't know the meaning of words, or my clothes aren't quite vogue or something. Maybe those girls in photography are ok to laugh at because they aren't polite to me. but apart from that i now propose that i shall not spend all media bagging everyone else in the class for having no brains. because they probably do have brains. 

and.

it's my birthday on friday. so strange. 17. my last year of innocence and getting away with things. i shall make the most of it. i have to. because as much as i want to turn 18, as soon as i'm 18 i'm going to not want to get old and wrinkly. 17 will be a fun age. it is decided. 

i am having a birthday brunch! hooray. even if it isn't on my birthday, which means that i won't be doing anything special on the actual celebration of the day i was born. just think. 17 years ago on friday i was some annoying crying brat. not a lot has changed eh?

apart from that life is usual. kids think i'm stalking them because i subconciously am. my ego has been inflated by people, hence i feel a sense of false security. and. (most importantly?) i'm going to the hairdresseers tomorrow. pretty hair!

1. In media today we were talking about world war 2 and americans joining the british
some idiot- "i sorta wish the american sided with the germans. so then they wouldn't be friendly with us now."
teacher - "umm well ... that's an interesting opinion. i guess it depends on how much if would affect us. and if you don't care about freedom."

2. In photography.
girl 1 - "make poverty history. what does that mean."
girl 2- "i dunno ive had it for like 2 years."
girl 1- "but poverty? what does it mean."
girl 2- "i think it's like when you're really poor and stuff and starving."
girl 1 -" i think i've got poverty then."


PEOPLE. SHE ACTUALLY SAID THAT SHE HAD POVERTY. ASFASJFDSKAF

there is a really dumb girl in my psych/media classes. she is from somewhere countryish and she just screams bogan. she even looks dumb.
and so the other day in media we were talking about how world war 1 started.
some person :" didn't it start because franz ferdinand was executed?"
country bogan: "isn't he like a singer or something?"
me: "*laughing* yeah. he makes songs AFTER his death. i wish i could do that."

well it was funny at the time

ok... a bunch of strange things.

1. on the bus (which was fucking packed) some snooty little punk was taking up her seat with her bag. i asked her nicely to move it and she got shitty. what the fuck? note to people- don't go to cheltenham secondary. they have attitude.

2. a girl from chelt asked me at bus stop for a cigarette. this bothers me because... smoking at bus stops is illegal... and i obviously look like the kind of kid who smokes. eww.

3. lunchtime was horrible. i was stuck with ajax (not the cleaning stuff...although that would be more fun) and yeah. until we discovered we both like cat and spent maths listening to them.

4. i have absoulety nothing to do all weekend. how terribly depressing.

5. I have a freaking Maths test ON MY BIRTHDAY. last 2 periods on a friday afternoon. what did i do to deserve such an injustice? FUCKING CUBICS.

So today i bought new cons.
My poor stripey ones may now be relegated to back of cupboard. But they shall never be forgotten. We've had many good times me and the stripeys. So many memories. And now they have been replaced. It is truly a sad day for humanity.

  RIP My poor cons. Dead and covered in clay. Eaten by Coco. Loved by all.


Replaced with.....
New cons. Snazzy and green.

Today i just wanted to kill photography. Everything. The camera, the teacher, the people. Alternatively i wanted to live in the mini mini darkroom. My negatives are scratched, and no matter how much glove wearing i do they do not come clean! 

Even an excellent and warm muffin couldn't solve my frustration.

This adds to the fact that i am still incredibly not over an certain someone, and it is my birthday soon approaching and i am far too lazy to sort something out, but i want to do SOMETHING.
